content:
#
# This is a Shiny web application. You can run the application by clicking
# the 'Run App' button above.
#
# Find out more about building applications with Shiny here:
#
#    https://shiny.posit.co/
#

library(shiny)
library(dplyr)
library(leaflet)
library(sf)


load('for_shiny_app')

geo = for_shiny_app |> group_by(place_id) |> summarise(n = n(), do_union = TRUE) |> select(-n)

for_shiny_app = for_shiny_app %>% mutate(inst_name = factor(inst_name)) |> 
  st_drop_geometry()

# Define UI for application that draws a histogram
ui <- fluidPage(

    # Application title
    titlePanel("STUDIUM"),

    # Sidebar with a slider input for number of bins 




        # Show a plot of the generated distribution
        mainPanel(
           leafletOutput("map")
        ,sliderInput('years', 'Years', min = 1426, max = 1800, value = c(1700, 1750),width = '100%'))
    )


# Define server logic required to draw a histogram
server <- function(input, output, session) {

  map_df = reactive({
    
    for_shiny_app %>%
      filter(year > input$years[1] & year < input$years[2]) %>%
      group_by(place_id, inst_name) %>%
      summarise(n = n()) |>
      left_join(geo, by = 'place_id') |> 
      st_as_sf()
    
  })
  
  
  output$map <- renderLeaflet({

     leaflet() |>
      addProviderTiles("Esri.WorldGrayCanvas") 
    
  })
  
  observe({
    leafletProxy("map", data = map_df()) |>
      clearShapes()|>
      addCircles()
      
  })
  
}

# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
